description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NORTHAMPTONSHIRE CENTRE FOR ONCOLOGY AND HAEMATOLOGY&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Staff Nurse/Junior Sister &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Talbot Butler Ward&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Come join our dynamic Oncology/Haematology Team here at NGH.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are committed to delivering high quality patient care through teams of dedicated, enthusiastic qualified staff. We are a friendly, professional team continually striving to deliver the best possible care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an organisation we will support you to develop yourself to enable you to identify improvements and the ability to make the changes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will support the Ward Manager in providing high quality care to cancer patients, admitted to the ward or attending the Emergency Assessment Bay. You will be responsible for leading a team of nurses, acting as an integral part of the cancer multidisciplinary team delivering individualised patient centered care and a seamless service to those affected by cancer.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We would welcome applications from highly motivated experienced cancer nurses who have considerable recent experience in caring for patients receiving oncological/haematological treatment or a willingness to learn . You will be committed to improving cancer care and willing to act as a driving force for change. The successful candidate needs to be able to cover all shifts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return we can offer you a stimulating work environment with a commitment to multidisciplinary working and continuing professional development. We offer a band 6 leadership course, chemotherapy course, MDT learning in simulation suite situations and opportunities for further development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Emma Cuthbert Job title: Ward Sister, Email address: emma.cuthbert@ngh.nhs.uk, Telephone number: 01604 545534&lt;/p&gt;
